'''Pangaea''' or '''Pangea''' (derived from Παγγαία, [[Ancient Greek|Greek]] meaning 'all earth') is the name given to the [[supercontinent]] that is believed to have existed during the [[Paleozoic]] and [[Mesozoic]] eras about 250 million years ago, before the process of [[plate tectonics]] separated each of the component [[continent]]s into their current configuration.

